09/02/2010
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Republika Srpska (RS) Prime Minister Milorad Dodik urged the entity's parliament Monday (February 8th) to pass a draft law on referendums as proposed by the government.
He said this version will be upheld by the Constitutional Court and relevant international organisations.
Opposition parties have said they want to amend it.
(Tanjug, RTRS, B92, Beta - 08/02/10)
